Figs.~\ref{fig:adp_curve} and~\ref{fig:runtime_curve} summarize the circuit-wise sequence optimization results on 60 benchmarks. Overall, the proposed framework achieves the best ADP on 50 out of 60 circuits, showing a clear advantage in final QoR. As shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:adp_curve}, the ADP values are normalized to FlowTune. On average, compared with the proposed framework, the final ADPs of FlowTune, BOiLS, and LOFMPL are 30.4\%, 13.8\%, and 8.5\% higher. This improvement is consistent with the design of our framework. First, the hybrid action space with macro actions exposes stronger multi-step optimization patterns than primitive-only search, which helps the optimizer explore higher-quality regions of the sequence space. Second, the LSTM-enhanced SSK kernel improves the GP surrogate by capturing not only symbolic subsequence overlap but also latent semantic similarity between synthesis sequences. Third, the auxiliary predictor provides area--delay-aware guidance during initialization and candidate filtering, which helps the search process focus on candidates with better overall QoR rather than favoring only one objective.

In addition to better ADP, the proposed framework also achieves substantially lower runtime. Its average runtime is only 2140\,s, compared with FlowTune, BOiLS, and LOFMPL, corresponding to runtime reductions of 94.0\%, 97.9\%, and 94.0\%. Moreover, the proposed framework does not hit the time limit on any benchmark, whereas FlowTune, BOiLS, and LOFMPL time out on 11, 60, and 6 circuits, respectively. This efficiency gain mainly comes from the predictor-enhanced search strategy. Instead of relying solely on expensive exact ABC evaluations, the proposed framework uses the auxiliary predictor for predictor-guided initialization, large-scale candidate pruning, and evaluation skipping before exact evaluation, thereby filtering out clearly unpromising sequences early. As a result, the Bayesian optimization loop can concentrate its evaluation budget on more promising candidates, significantly reducing unnecessary oracle calls and leading to much faster convergence in practice.

