\section{Conclusion}

In this paper, we propose a predictor-enhanced Bayesian optimization framework for logic synthesis sequence search. The proposed framework combines an AIG-derived unified circuit representation, a hybrid action space with macro actions and \textsc{nop}-based variable-length encoding, a multi-task predictor for joint area and delay estimation, and an LSTM-enhanced SSK kernel for discrete surrogate modeling. By tightly integrating the predictor into the optimization loop for warm-start initialization, candidate pruning, and evaluation skipping, the framework improves both search quality and efficiency while reducing expensive exact evaluations. Experimental results on EPFL, OpenABC-D, and VTR benchmarks show that the proposed framework achieves the best ADP on 50 out of 60 circuits, reduces the final ADP by 30.4\%, 13.8\%, and 8.5\% compared with FlowTune, BOiLS, and LOFMPL, and delivers more than 15$\times$ speedup.


